      • select

        protected int select
        If not -1, select is the "anchor point" of a selection. That is, if you hit shift+left with no existing selection, the selection will be anchored to where you were, but the cursor will move left, expanding the selection as you continue to move left. If you move to the right, eventually you'll overtake the anchor, drop the anchor at the same place and start expanding the selection rightwards instead.
